cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper deals with privacy definitions and mechanisms for statistical databases, which are relevant to the fields of cryptography (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures (cs.DS), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper specifically focuses on privacy-utility trade-offs and policies for extending differential privacy, which are topics that are commonly studied in these sub-categories.
